Author: Sultan6996
Title: iOS 13.1 Required?!
Review: The app for some reason demands that the iPhone have the latest iOS version which is not available on iPhone 6. Why should I be rejected entry to even the grocery store just because I have an older phone that doesn’t download this demanding app. It apparently is the LAW to download this app or you will be fined, and yet the sheer inconvenience that comes with this app makes it that much harder to live here during the pandemic. On top of that, the app took data that it wasn’t supposed to from phones, compromising privacy unnecessarily, and that was supposedly “fixed” but it was not even addressed in the update history. Privacy is a basic human right, and I should not sacrifice my privacy for the sake of an app that could operate just as well without sucking information from my phone.

Author: Lord_Faz
Title: Major update needed
Review:
For an app that tracks and can tell if in close proximity (with everyone having to have Bluetooth and location setting on all the time) there should be a localised map so you can see how close you are to other people and their status colour. Only notifications in this app are announcements. If there is a close proximity alert then you are only told in notification centre - no way of reading the notification in the app as like I said only announcements can be seen in the in-app notification section. 

you should be able to set your home and work location so it stops Bluetooth and location tracking when at these 2 set points because there is a major battery drain due to this app needing to always be on.

Please take this review as constructive feedback and update accordingly.
